    "body": "Hello !\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if this have ever been discussed, I haven't found any issue with this. I'm also not 100% certain its not possible with workaround right now.\r\n\r\nWould it be possible to have a feature to load config and plugins (Have the ~/.config/nvim) embeddable in the appimage ? That would be really neat as this would mean we could configure neovim the way we like, build an appimage with this config embedded and simply download it on any computer / server we use.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if this would be easily doable but it would be a really interesting feature",
