            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I'm bringing up this old thread but I still not managed to do it for some reason. \r\n\r\nWhen I do `:echo $VIM` I get this path: `/tmp/.mount_NeovimWaIcT9/usr/share/nvim`\r\nSo I added a `sysinit.vim` as you said in the appimage at `AppImageDir/usr/share/nvim/sysinit.vim` and repacked it.\r\n\r\nIt does not get loaded. I also checked the `-V` arg to find a not used file, and it tells me it can't load `/etc/xdg/nvim/init.vim` so I tried putting it there in the appimage and it also does not work.\r\n\r\nIt DOES work when I append it to an existing file which gets loaded (e.g. `AppImage/usr/share/nvim/runtime/syntax/syntax.vim`) but I'd rather do it properly\r\n\r\nAny clue ?\r\n\r\nEDIT: `nvim.appimage -V` gives me only two path that it tried to load but failed, none of them are in the appimage mounted directory:\r\n```\r\nimpossible de sourcer \"/home/oxodao/.config/nvim/init.vim\"\r\nimpossible de sourcer \"/etc/xdg//nvim/init.vim\"\r\n```",
