            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Ok so I found a way, I'm not that fond of it but it does work for now. Not sure how I would put my whole config in it (Like with plugin & such) but it will do the job for now.\r\n\r\nIf anyone want to do the same here's my solution:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ ./nvim.appimage --appimage-extract\r\n```\r\n\r\nReplace the AppRun with this content (We basically just tell vim it should run with a given config file, in the mounted path of the appimage):\r\n```\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\n\r\nexport ROOT_PATH=\"$(dirname \"$(readlink -f \"${0}\")\")\"\r\n\r\nunset ARGV0\r\nexec \"$ROOT_PATH/usr/bin/nvim\" \"-u\" \"$ROOT_PATH/vimcfg/vimrc\" ${@+\"$@\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nCreate the folder: `$ mkdir squashfs-root/vimcfg`\r\nPut your config in `$PWD/squashfs-root/vimcfg/vimrc`\r\n\r\nFinally, rebuild the image: `$ appimagetool -n squashfs-root`\r\n\r\nYou will have an appimage with your embedded config.\r\n\r\nNow I need to figure out how to embed plugins and use multiple files without too much hacks",
